                <h1>The Power of Metaphors in The Yellow Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>In "The Yellow Wallpaper," the narrator's descent into madness is eloquently depicted through vivid metaphors. The wallpaper itself symbolizes societal oppression and the constraints placed on women's autonomy. As she becomes obsessed with the patterns, they represent her struggles for identity and freedom, ultimately reflecting her mental deterioration.</p>
